Abstract
This project provides an upgraded Library Management System constructed using the C programming language.
Unlike basic systems that store books simply in memory, this system delivers capabilities closer to a real-world library process.

It enables users to:
â€¢	Update the system with fresh books
â€¢	Look up books by author, title, or ID.
â€¢	Issue and return books
â€¢	Keep the last borrower's name on file.
â€¢	Display library statistics such as total books and copies


Problem Definition
Libraries have to manage a lot of books, which is challenging if done by hand. Popular actions like verifying availability or issuing a book become error-prone when done with pen and paper.

A basic digital management system ought to:
â€¢	Organise book information cleanly
â€¢	Permit quick searching
â€¢	Track available copies
â€¢	Keep borrower information up to date
â€¢	Maintain records even after they are shut down.

This project's primary goal is to create a straightforward but enhanced library system that shows how fundamental C principles can be used to solve real-world issues.
